==English==

===Alternative forms===
* {{l|en|bat one thousand}}

===Etymology===
From a [[baseball]] [[batting average]], often stated as the number of [[hit]]s per 1000 [[at bat]]s- 1000 would be [[100 percent]].

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|en|en-au-bat a thousand.ogg|Audio (AU)}}

===Verb===
{{en-verb|head=[[bat]] a [[thousand]]|*}}

# {{lb|en|baseball}} To reach first base on every [[at-bat]].
# {{lb|en|idiomatic}} To achieve success at each attempt.
#: {{ux|en|He's '''batting a thousand''' so far with the new boss.}}
# {{lb|en|idiomatic}} To achieve perfection.
#: {{ux|en|No one can '''bat a thousand''' for the whole season.}}
# {{lb|en|idiomatic}} To have identical outcomes on each attempt

